  saturated fat: 6 g
  carbohydrates: 31 g
  sugar: 8 g
  protein: 39 g
  fiber: 6 g
  sodium: 1530 mg
servings: 2
---

Wash and dry produce.

Core, deseed, and dice @green bell pepper{1} into ½-inch pieces. Trim and quarter @button mushrooms{4%oz} (skip if your mushrooms are pre-sliced!). Trim and halve @zucchini{1}; cut crosswise into ½-inch-thick half-moons. Halve @grape tomatoes{4%oz}. Peel and mince or grate @garlic{2%clove}. Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}, separating whites from greens.

Transfer ½ tsp @nutritional yeast{2%tablespoon} (1 tsp for 4 servings) to a small #bowl{}; set aside for serving. (You'll use the rest of the nutritional yeast in Step 3!)

== Sautéed Vegetables ==

Heat a large drizzle of @olive oil{} in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add bell pepper, mushrooms, and zucchini; season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Cook, stirring occasionally, until veggies are browned and just softened, ~{5-7%minutes}. TIP: While veggies cook, move on to Step 3!

In the last minute of cooking, add tomatoes and garlic; cook, stirring, until fragrant, ~{30%seconds}.

Add 2 TBSP @water{2%TBSP} (4 TBSP for 4) and cook, stirring constantly, until liquid has mostly reduced, about ~{1%minute}. Season with salt and pepper.

== Polenta ==

While veggies cook, heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{} in a #small pot{} over medium heat. Add scallion whites and cook, stirring occasionally, until fragrant, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Add @precooked polenta{1} and @veggie stock concentrate{1}, and ⅓ cup @water{⅓%cup} (⅔ cup for 4 servings). Mash with a #potato masher{} or #fork{} until mostly smooth, ~{30-60%seconds}.

Add remaining nutritional yeast and cook, stirring, until thickened and warmed through, ~{4-5%minutes}. Taste and season with salt and pepper if desired. TIP: If polenta seems too thick, add water 1 TBSP at a time until it reaches desired consistency.

== To Serve ==

Divide polenta between shallow #bowls{}{}.

Top with sautéed veggies. Sprinkle with reserved nutritional yeast and scallion greens. Serve.

> Fish is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 145°.